 <BR><img src=http://members.ozemail.com.au/~dkowalec/blackmagesig.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Would anyone really object a DAoC skill system as AAXP?</span><hr size=1> I liked the DAoC skill system, I really thought that was how the AAXP system was supposed to have turned out. It seems more drawn out and created more specialty between the classes and characters. If done right Planes of Power can implement a system like this where we gain skill points via quests, exp, and other activities. What do you think? Too much taken from DAoC? I mean gettin particular skills or spells in a tree like form would be very class/character defining. <p><div align=center> Deaddragoxo Spiritbound 43 necro <BR> <div align=center> Scaleyfists Witfungfugrip 24 monk <BR> <div align=center> Guild Event Coordinator of Clan Phoenix-Everquest-Xegony <BR> <div align=center> www.clanphoenix.org <BR> <div align=center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uluzondaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LuzonDAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 10:31:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23334.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would anyone really object a DAoC skill system as AAXP?</span><hr size=1> If they are going to steal from DAoC, I'd rather see things like the anti-train code and the /stick command.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umalqanar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malqanar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 10:41:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23334.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/saladin/malqanar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would anyone really object a DAoC skill system as AAXP?</span><hr size=1> A system where you've got limited points to spend can be tricky to balance though. DAoC has/had it's fair share of problems with regards to &quot;gimped&quot; characters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udeaddragoxo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deaddragoxo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 11:02:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23334.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.ozemail.com.au/~dkowalec/blackmagesig.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would anyone really object a DAoC skill system as AAXP?</span><hr size=1> ya thats the main issue that I see but I think they have enough time to decipher the system. I agree with the whole non training thing but I doubt that would ever happen. Only because of the fact that EQ was based on risk vs reward, taking away trains would sorta be against VI's scheme of things. They would rather we had trains because it causes us to think if its worth it or not. Personally I agree though. <p><div align=center> Deaddragoxo Spiritbound 43 necro <BR> <div align=center> Scaleyfists Witfungfugrip 24 monk <BR> <div align=center> Guild Event Coordinator of Clan Phoenix-Everquest-Xegony <BR> <div align=center> www.clanphoenix.org <BR> <div align=center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueuripedmoped.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euriped Moped</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 11:41:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23334.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~yolora/zdance.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would anyone really object a DAoC skill system as AAXP?</span><hr size=1> DAoC system doesn't work well.  I have a level 45 enchanter on the Merlin server. They messed with my class long, long after I had gone through specializing (which means putting almost all my points) into Enchantment Mastery.  I had worked it so that I would get every spell except those in the very last circle. <br>
<br>
Anyway.  Then they altered the way my class works, making it so that Enchant spec'ed enchanters were truly not as good as those spec'd in mana or light.  Net effect? I quit the game.  I had put time and effort into this character, and I was happy with the results (and I do mean happy as a damned clam), and people complained that some of us were, god forbid, having fun.  They didn't roll back my spec points so that I could spend them in one of the other lines.  It pissed me off.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, I don't think you should be skill limited. Everything should be automatic. Improvement should come from items and spells, not skill ups.. unless you can skill up in everything. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufeochadan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feochadan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 11:47:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23334.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would anyone really object a DAoC skill system as AAXP?</span><hr size=1> DAoC has fully integrated trivial loot code (you never get loot from &quot;gray&quot; mobs and only 1 exp). People want that too in EQ ?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Feochadan Shadowleaf<BR>
Assassin, Wrath of Tunare<BR>Cazic-Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uswanda08.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swanda08</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/17/02 2:47:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23334.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://broodwar.gcpro.de/fun/fanart/Kyron2_tn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would anyone really object a DAoC skill system as AAXP?</span><hr size=1> TLC would have been great if it came from day 1 tho :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udeathbane27.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deathbane27</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/17/02 8:54:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23334.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jediassassins.f2s.com/imgs/icon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would anyone really object a DAoC skill system as AAXP?</span><hr size=1> I would find it good IF you had a way to reset your spec points.  DAoC did not.<br>
<br>
DAoC's loot and death penalty was designed with the TLC in mind.  You never lost your items unless you deliberately gave them away.  You could still get quest items from grey mobs.  Greens (light blues in EQ) were easy enough to beat so that you didn't really feel irritated about the TLC except in the few cases of too-rare items that only dropped off monsters in a certain level range and for which there were no upgrades (aka bowmaster bracers).  EQ has similar problems.  Every item would have to be reworked as far as price and drop rate go if EQ were to have TLC on every item.  I will never play on Firiona Vie. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usilaena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silaena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/17/02 9:11:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23334.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would anyone really object a DAoC skill system as AAXP?</span><hr size=1> TLC on FV work pretty fine and is good for server economy, except for Quest item, they really should do something about it.<br>
<br>
